{title: An Evening Prayer}
{artist: Mel Tillis | Country Gospel}
{composer: written by}

[C]If I have wounded some [G7]poor soul [F]today
If [G7]I have caused one foot to [C]go a[G7]stray
If [C]I have walked in my own [F]willful way
Dear [C]Lord   [G7]for-[C]give

If I have uttered idle [G7]words in [F]vain
If [G7]I have turned aside from [C]want or [G7]pain
Lest [C]I offend some other [F]through the strain
Dear [C]Lord   [G7]for-[C]give

If I have been perverse or [G7]hard or [F]cold
If [G7]I have longed for shelter [C]in Thy [G7]fold
When [C]Thou hast given me some [F]fort to hold
Dear [C]Lord  [G7]for-[C]give

Forgive these sins I have con[G7]fessed to [F]Thee
For[G7]give the secret sins I [C]do not [G7]see
[C]Guide me  love me and my [F]keeper be
Dear [C]Lord  [G7]for-[C]give